   <abstract>Clarence Brown playing a reporter in "The Acquittal." The movie tells the story of Andrew Prentice (Charles Wellesley) who has two unrelated adopted sons: Kenneth Winthrop (Richard Travers) and Robert Armstrong (Norman Kerry). Winthrop is married to Madeline Ames (Claire Windsor). When Prentice is found dead, Winthrop is charged with and acquitted of the crime. Thus, it falls to Madeline to find the real killer.</abstract>
